<span id="xv.iv.iv.lxxxix"></span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lxxxix-p1"></span> <span class="c4"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.lxxxix-p1.1"></span>Canon LXXXVIII.  (Greek xci.)</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lxxxix-p2"></span>Of Maximian, the bishop.

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lxxxix-p3"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.lxxxix-p3.1"></span>But</span> in the case of Maximian of
Vagai <span id="fr_466"></span>[467](#fn_466.md) it seemed good that
letters be sent from the council both to him and to his people; that he
should vacate the bishoprick, and that they should request another to be
appointed for them.

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lxxxix-p5"></span><span class="c4"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.lxxxix-p5.1"></span>Notes.</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lxxxix-p6"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.lxxxix-p6.1"></span>Ancient Epitome of Canon
LXXXVIII.</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lxxxix-p7"></span>Let Maximian of Bagai be expelled
from his church, and another be set in his room.

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lxxxix-p8"></span>This canon is remaining part of
Canon ij., of the Synod of Milevis, <span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.lxxxix-p8.1"></span>a.d.</span> 402.

